1
00:00:10,433 --> 00:00:11,533
<i> Why are you hiding?</i>

2
00:00:11,667 --> 00:00:12,833
<i> Aren't you working here?</i>

3
00:00:12,967 --> 00:00:14,367
<i>Major and I just made that up
for a show,</i>

4
00:00:14,500 --> 00:00:15,433
<i> that's why you should leave.</i>

5
00:00:15,567 --> 00:00:16,767
<i> This is what I'm telling you.</i>

6
00:00:16,900 --> 00:00:17,900
<i> Trust the process.</i>

7
00:00:18,033 --> 00:00:19,133
<i>Because if too many people
find out,</i>

8
00:00:19,267 --> 00:00:21,133
<i> Conde will be compromised.</i>

9
00:00:21,267 --> 00:00:22,433
<i> That's enough!</i>

10
00:00:22,567 --> 00:00:23,933
<i>The election
is already my problem,</i>

11
00:00:24,067 --> 00:00:25,000
<i> you're going to add to it!</i>

12
00:00:25,133 --> 00:00:27,000
<i> Why are we having dinner here?</i>

13
00:00:27,133 --> 00:00:29,033
<i> I'm courting Leslie, remember?</i>

14
00:00:29,167 --> 00:00:31,300
<i>I just want to make
a better impression.</i>

15
00:00:31,433 --> 00:00:33,667
<i>This is Vice Mayor Leslie
Del Mundo.</i>

16
00:00:33,800 --> 00:00:34,600
<i> I won't vote for him.</i>

17
00:00:34,767 --> 00:00:35,767
<i> I don't like his wife.</i>

18
00:00:35,900 --> 00:00:38,367
<i> I called to tell you...</i>

19
00:00:38,500 --> 00:00:39,733
<i> that I saw Cecilia.</i>

20
00:00:39,867 --> 00:00:41,033
<i> I'll talk to her.</i>

21
00:00:41,167 --> 00:00:42,300
<i> What? Have you seen them?</i>

22
00:00:42,433 --> 00:00:43,400
<i> Not yet.</i>

23
00:00:44,833 --> 00:00:46,400
<i>You're strong, but you're slow!</i>

24
00:00:47,733 --> 00:00:49,367
<i> I said...</i>

25
00:00:50,233 --> 00:00:51,500
<i> Don't!</i>

26
00:00:51,633 --> 00:00:52,300
<i> Let's go!</i>

27
00:00:52,433 --> 00:00:53,433
<i> What happened to your face?</i>

28
00:00:53,567 --> 00:00:55,367
<i>Could that be a targeted attack?</i>

29
00:00:55,500 --> 00:00:57,100
<i>Eric, I'll just go
to the washroom, okay?</i>

30
00:00:57,233 --> 00:00:58,267
<i> Oh, okay.</i>

31
00:00:58,400 --> 00:01:00,400
<i>Vice Mayor Del Mundo
will announce tomorrow</i>

32
00:01:00,533 --> 00:01:02,933
<i>that she will be supporting dad
as her mayor.</i>

33
00:01:03,067 --> 00:01:05,233
<i>I'll take care of it.
I have an IED supplier.</i>

34
00:01:19,467 --> 00:01:21,300
<i> Why would you do that?</i>

35
00:01:21,433 --> 00:01:24,567
<i>I just had my people follow you.</i>

36
00:01:24,700 --> 00:01:25,733
I don't know if that idiot cop
you're dating...

37
00:01:25,867 --> 00:01:28,000
is taking you to a motel.

38
00:01:28,767 --> 00:01:31,033
I didn't know he was going
to fight back.

39
00:01:31,167 --> 00:01:34,600
That's why he got beaten up.

40
00:01:34,733 --> 00:01:36,000
Why?

41
00:01:36,133 --> 00:01:39,367
<i>I can't go on a date
without you following me?</i>

42
00:01:39,500 --> 00:01:41,400
<i> Yes, of course.</i>

43
00:01:41,567 --> 00:01:42,633
Up to you.

44
00:01:42,767 --> 00:01:44,933
You can date other people,

45
00:01:45,733 --> 00:01:47,733
but they'll only get in danger.

46
00:01:49,567 --> 00:01:51,267
So you're mine.

47
00:01:59,767 --> 00:02:00,733
Oh...

48
00:02:00,867 --> 00:02:03,167
Sergeant Enriquez?

49
00:02:04,767 --> 00:02:06,400
Were you there
for a long time now?

50
00:02:07,567 --> 00:02:09,733
No, Doc, I just got here.

51
00:02:09,867 --> 00:02:11,500
I'll also use the restroom.

52
00:02:12,467 --> 00:02:14,967
- Okay, okay.
- Okay.

53
00:03:32,067 --> 00:03:34,833
What you did to Lieutenant
Garcia is still wrong.

54
00:03:35,867 --> 00:03:37,833
Don't tell me you're falling
for him.

55
00:03:41,433 --> 00:03:43,633
Eric is kind, Glen.

56
00:03:43,767 --> 00:03:45,567
He's harmless.

57
00:03:46,200 --> 00:03:50,100
Cecilia, no police officer
is harmless.

58
00:03:51,500 --> 00:03:53,733
What's the update on...

59
00:03:53,900 --> 00:03:55,667
what we're doing
to Godfather Victor?

60
00:03:55,800 --> 00:03:57,500
Has anyone else had any doubts?

61
00:03:59,133 --> 00:04:02,400
Until now, they still have
no idea,

62
00:04:02,533 --> 00:04:04,533
that I doctored
the ballistic report...

63
00:04:04,667 --> 00:04:06,767
connecting Victor Santiago...

64
00:04:06,900 --> 00:04:09,233
to the bullet found
in Bullet's head.

65
00:04:09,367 --> 00:04:11,100
But...

66
00:04:11,233 --> 00:04:15,000
don't you think what you're
doing to Amo is overkill?

67
00:04:15,133 --> 00:04:16,400
No.

68
00:04:16,533 --> 00:04:20,500
Not until dad is back
as mayor of Calabari.

69
00:04:21,733 --> 00:04:23,533
And then?

70
00:04:23,667 --> 00:04:26,067
And then on to my next plan.

71
00:04:28,500 --> 00:04:30,933
If only the people
at Station 12 knew

72
00:04:31,067 --> 00:04:33,633
they were investigating
the wrong person.

73
00:04:37,033 --> 00:04:39,233
That's why you're there.

74
00:04:42,933 --> 00:04:46,400
To keep them looking
in the wrong direction.

75
00:04:57,767 --> 00:04:58,933
Give them some more!

76
00:04:59,067 --> 00:05:01,167
Guys, that's on the house.

77
00:05:01,333 --> 00:05:03,100
I'll take care of that.
Oh, just take it.

78
00:05:03,233 --> 00:05:05,500
That's Sir Eric's treat!

79
00:05:05,633 --> 00:05:08,400
- Bok, is it your birthday?
- Here, just take it.

80
00:05:08,533 --> 00:05:10,733
No, but...

81
00:05:10,867 --> 00:05:12,433
I'm just happy.

82
00:05:12,567 --> 00:05:13,733
Why, Sir?

83
00:05:13,867 --> 00:05:15,800
Has Doc answered you already?

84
00:05:15,933 --> 00:05:18,900
The question is,
what will be Doc's answer?

85
00:05:19,033 --> 00:05:20,367
Probably, the answer is no.

86
00:05:21,633 --> 00:05:22,600
Hey, hey, hey.

87
00:05:22,733 --> 00:05:24,267
Those three, you charge them.

88
00:05:24,400 --> 00:05:25,933
- That's not included.
- It's not funny anymore.

89
00:05:26,067 --> 00:05:27,133
Come on.

90
00:05:27,267 --> 00:05:29,133
Well, you guys, you don't have
any confidence for me.

91
00:05:29,267 --> 00:05:32,533
Of course, I told Doc,
that we'll just take it slow.

92
00:05:32,667 --> 00:05:35,400
I want to take things slow,

93
00:05:35,567 --> 00:05:38,900
because I want to cherish
the moments.

94
00:05:39,400 --> 00:05:40,933
- Sir.
- Oh?

95
00:05:41,600 --> 00:05:43,800
Can I talk to you?

96
00:05:43,933 --> 00:05:45,667
Oh, yes.

97
00:05:47,300 --> 00:05:48,967
Sir...

98
00:05:49,100 --> 00:05:50,967
because I have a feeling...

99
00:05:51,100 --> 00:05:53,633
Doc Ces knows the person
who robbed you.

100
00:05:54,800 --> 00:05:57,233
Because I heard her in the
restroom talking to someone.

101
00:05:57,367 --> 00:05:58,933
She's angry.

102
00:06:00,700 --> 00:06:02,533
Could it be her ex-boyfriend,
Ma'am?

103
00:06:02,667 --> 00:06:04,900
Oh my, you should
get nervous, Bok.

104
00:06:05,033 --> 00:06:07,667
Doc's ex-boyfriend
seems to be big-time.

105
00:06:23,533 --> 00:06:25,367
Oh, here, here.

106
00:06:25,933 --> 00:06:29,033
Hurry up and we'll ask them.

107
00:06:29,167 --> 00:06:30,800
Where are you going?
To the rally?

108
00:06:30,933 --> 00:06:31,933
Oh, okay, here.

109
00:06:32,067 --> 00:06:33,733
Hurry up.

110
00:06:36,033 --> 00:06:37,000
<i>Okay, Miss, the one
in the t-shirt.</i>

111
00:06:37,133 --> 00:06:38,600
<i>There, the ones in the t-shirt.</i>

112
00:06:38,733 --> 00:06:40,867
Sir, Sir, you're not allowed
to pass through here.

113
00:06:41,000 --> 00:06:42,300
We're sorry.

114
00:06:42,467 --> 00:06:43,900
Why? What's going on?

115
00:06:44,033 --> 00:06:48,100
Mayor Joaquin has
a big political rally.

116
00:06:48,233 --> 00:06:50,333
It's going to be held there
near the open gymnasium later.

117
00:06:50,467 --> 00:06:53,067
So, Sir, we're redirecting
the traffic.

118
00:06:53,200 --> 00:06:54,267
Just back up, Sir.

119
00:06:54,400 --> 00:06:55,800
We're sorry.

120
00:06:57,667 --> 00:06:59,267
Okay.

121
00:07:03,200 --> 00:07:04,567
Oh.

122
00:07:06,067 --> 00:07:07,600
What's with you?

123
00:07:08,267 --> 00:07:09,967
Enriquez...

124
00:07:10,933 --> 00:07:13,300
are you jealous again?

125
00:07:13,433 --> 00:07:15,600
Can you please move on now?

126
00:07:15,767 --> 00:07:18,233
Because I've moved on.

127
00:07:18,367 --> 00:07:21,200
Let me be free, okay?

128
00:07:22,333 --> 00:07:24,967
Sir, it's up to you.

129
00:07:25,100 --> 00:07:26,433
Well,

130
00:07:27,333 --> 00:07:28,933
I'm just saying.

131
00:07:29,400 --> 00:07:31,700
You still have to be careful,
Sir.

132
00:07:31,833 --> 00:07:32,700
Okay.

133
00:07:32,833 --> 00:07:33,767
I'm really sorry.

134
00:07:33,900 --> 00:07:35,567
I have nothing more to give.

135
00:07:35,700 --> 00:07:36,967
Okay, okay.

136
00:07:42,167 --> 00:07:44,400
Poor Enriquez.

137
00:07:45,367 --> 00:07:48,233
She's still very much
in love with me.

138
00:07:52,967 --> 00:07:53,967
Hello, Dad?

139
00:07:54,100 --> 00:07:55,167
<i> Hello, Son? What?</i>

140
00:07:55,300 --> 00:07:56,600
Is Roman still there?

141
00:07:56,733 --> 00:07:59,967
Oh, he just came out, and I gave
him orders to do something.

142
00:08:00,667 --> 00:08:02,067
<i> I'll take care of it.</i>

143
00:08:02,200 --> 00:08:03,833
<i> I'll plant it tomorrow too.</i>

144
00:08:03,967 --> 00:08:06,400
<i> I have an IED supplier.</i>

145
00:08:06,533 --> 00:08:09,067
Oh, is that so?
What did you ask him to do?

146
00:08:09,200 --> 00:08:11,300
I'm not doing anything.
Maybe I can accompany him.

147
00:08:11,433 --> 00:08:14,367
Oh, no need.

148
00:08:14,500 --> 00:08:16,067
Roman can handle that.

149
00:08:19,600 --> 00:08:24,867
I just wanted to talk to him,
Dad, so we can patch things up.

150
00:08:26,167 --> 00:08:28,300
Okay, never mind.
I'll just call him.

151
00:08:29,433 --> 00:08:31,267
Oh, okay.

152
00:08:48,567 --> 00:08:49,967
Hello, Sir?

153
00:08:50,100 --> 00:08:51,600
Hello, Enriquez?

154
00:08:52,167 --> 00:08:53,867
Listen.

155
00:08:54,500 --> 00:08:57,033
I heard Roman, he was talking
to someone last night.

156
00:08:57,567 --> 00:08:59,700
<i>He said he had
a supplier of IED.</i>

157
00:08:59,833 --> 00:09:01,533
<i>He said he would
plant it himself.</i>

158
00:09:02,300 --> 00:09:04,000
Now, I followed him.

159
00:09:04,133 --> 00:09:07,300
He was on his way to Mayor
Guerrero's political rally.

160
00:09:07,433 --> 00:09:08,400
Wait, wait a minute, Sir.

161
00:09:08,533 --> 00:09:10,100
What did you say?

162
00:09:11,500 --> 00:09:13,100
I think there's a bomb...

163
00:09:13,867 --> 00:09:16,833
going off at the
political rally.

164
00:09:17,933 --> 00:09:19,567
What?

165
00:09:19,700 --> 00:09:21,533
Are you sure, Sir?

166
00:09:22,867 --> 00:09:24,533
No...

167
00:09:25,300 --> 00:09:27,333
<i> but I have a strong feeling.</i>

168
00:09:30,233 --> 00:09:32,500
I need your help, Enriquez.

169
00:09:33,633 --> 00:09:35,367
Okay, Sir.

170
00:09:48,300 --> 00:09:49,433
Oh, you're going to the rally?
The rally?

171
00:09:49,567 --> 00:09:52,333
Okay, just go straight.

172
00:09:52,467 --> 00:09:54,067
<i> You, Mister?</i>

173
00:09:54,200 --> 00:09:55,600
Oh, okay, okay.

174
00:09:55,733 --> 00:09:58,100
<i>Miss, Mister,
you're not in uniform.</i>

175
00:09:59,967 --> 00:10:01,100
Are you attending the rally?

176
00:10:01,267 --> 00:10:02,833
Oh, okay, okay.

177
00:10:10,300 --> 00:10:11,967
Look, there are politicians
here, oh.

178
00:10:12,100 --> 00:10:13,433
- Yes, there's a lot of people.
- Let's go this way.

179
00:10:13,567 --> 00:10:15,167
It's Boss Tonyo.
Oh, Boss Tonyo!

180
00:10:15,300 --> 00:10:16,300
- Boss Tonyo!
- Boss Tonyo!

181
00:10:16,433 --> 00:10:18,167
- We haven't seen each other.
- Boss, what's up?

182
00:10:18,300 --> 00:10:19,700
- Any news?
- We miss you, Boss.

183
00:10:19,833 --> 00:10:20,933
Don't we have a racket there?

184
00:10:21,067 --> 00:10:23,133
No, no, wait,
I have a question.

185
00:10:23,267 --> 00:10:24,800
Do you know the head
of security here?

186
00:10:24,933 --> 00:10:27,000
Boss, no, but we can
find out for you.

187
00:10:27,133 --> 00:10:28,100
Oh, yeah, we can.

188
00:10:28,233 --> 00:10:32,000
Excuse me, I have
a favor to ask you.

189
00:10:32,133 --> 00:10:33,067
I need your help...

190
00:10:33,200 --> 00:10:35,767
because I can't talk
to anyone inside.

191
00:10:35,933 --> 00:10:38,933
I need your help
to warn the people

192
00:10:39,067 --> 00:10:40,200
that there's a bomb in there.

193
00:10:40,333 --> 00:10:41,233
- Oh, bomb?
- Bomb?

194
00:10:41,367 --> 00:10:43,467
Don't make any noise!

195
00:10:43,600 --> 00:10:45,167
People might panic.

196
00:10:45,300 --> 00:10:46,967
So go ahead and tell
the security there

197
00:10:47,100 --> 00:10:48,167
what I said, okay.

198
00:10:48,300 --> 00:10:49,067
Okay, okay, okay, Boss.

199
00:10:49,200 --> 00:10:50,200
Come on! Come on!

200
00:10:50,333 --> 00:10:53,267
Boss, are you sure
there's a bomb inside?

201
00:10:57,300 --> 00:10:58,733
Faye.

202
00:11:07,533 --> 00:11:08,967
Noble!

203
00:11:09,133 --> 00:11:10,533
Come on, come with me.

204
00:11:11,000 --> 00:11:12,767
Where are we going, Ma'am?

205
00:11:12,900 --> 00:11:13,967
Sir Tonyo called.

206
00:11:14,100 --> 00:11:15,833
They said there might be a bomb
at the Mayor's rally.

207
00:11:15,967 --> 00:11:18,100
Huh? Is Sir Tonyo sure?

208
00:11:18,233 --> 00:11:19,700
I don't know,

209
00:11:19,833 --> 00:11:21,800
but we need to get
those people out of there

210
00:11:21,933 --> 00:11:22,600
whether there's a bomb or not.

211
00:11:22,733 --> 00:11:24,167
Come on!

212
00:11:24,700 --> 00:11:25,567
Put it in.

213
00:11:25,700 --> 00:11:27,500
Jenny, give it inside.

214
00:11:27,633 --> 00:11:28,733
Mr. Romy!

215
00:11:28,867 --> 00:11:29,833
We're going to tell you
something,

216
00:11:29,967 --> 00:11:31,133
but don't be surprised, okay?

217
00:11:31,267 --> 00:11:32,200
- What's that?
- Mr. Romy,

218
00:11:32,333 --> 00:11:34,000
someone gave us information.

219
00:11:34,133 --> 00:11:35,667
- They said there's a bomb here.
- Yes, there is.

220
00:11:35,800 --> 00:11:36,833
- Bomb?
- Yes, yes!

221
00:11:36,967 --> 00:11:37,767
Yes, Mr. Romy.

222
00:11:37,900 --> 00:11:39,267
Hey, you two.

223
00:11:39,400 --> 00:11:40,367
That's not a good joke.

224
00:11:40,500 --> 00:11:42,300
- We're not joking!
- We're not!

225
00:11:42,467 --> 00:11:43,733
Hey, Mr. Romy,
we need to get

226
00:11:43,867 --> 00:11:45,400
those people out as soon
as possible.

227
00:11:45,533 --> 00:11:46,733
Yes, Sir, you take care of it.

228
00:11:46,867 --> 00:11:47,933
We have somewhere else to go.

229
00:11:48,067 --> 00:11:49,767
- Okay.
- Sir.

230
00:11:50,700 --> 00:11:51,800
Hi!

231
00:11:51,933 --> 00:11:54,967
Thank you very much for
your support to my daddy.

232
00:11:55,933 --> 00:11:56,900
- Thank you, Ma'am.
- Thank you.

233
00:11:57,033 --> 00:11:58,300
- Can we take a picture?
- Oh, okay, let's go.

234
00:11:58,433 --> 00:11:59,533
- Picture.
- Picture, picture, quick.

235
00:12:01,067 --> 00:12:03,200
<i> Thank you, see you later.</i>

236
00:12:03,333 --> 00:12:04,767
Thank you.

237
00:12:04,900 --> 00:12:07,167
Thank you, thank you.

238
00:12:09,700 --> 00:12:11,467
<i> What?</i>

239
00:12:11,600 --> 00:12:13,167
Are you sure?

240
00:12:14,967 --> 00:12:17,300
Okay, I'll tell him.

241
00:12:17,433 --> 00:12:18,867
Dad...

242
00:12:19,000 --> 00:12:20,733
the head of security,
called me.

243
00:12:20,867 --> 00:12:21,967
There was a bomb threat.

244
00:12:22,100 --> 00:12:23,267
- What?
- Glen...

245
00:12:23,400 --> 00:12:25,400
Who said that?

246
00:12:25,533 --> 00:12:27,033
I don't know,
one of the supporters.

247
00:12:27,167 --> 00:12:29,333
Oh, my, that's fake.

248
00:12:29,467 --> 00:12:31,100
Don't believe that.

249
00:12:31,233 --> 00:12:33,600
This event is just
being sabotaged.

250
00:12:33,733 --> 00:12:36,333
Dad, I think we need
to take things seriously.

251
00:12:36,467 --> 00:12:38,267
I need to call
the bomb squad.

252
00:12:38,400 --> 00:12:40,367
No, no, no, Glen.

253
00:12:40,500 --> 00:12:42,200
You're just scaring
my supporters.

254
00:12:42,333 --> 00:12:44,200
- Chuck, come here.
- Sir?

255
00:12:45,300 --> 00:12:51,233
Tell our people whoever's making
those bomb jokes, catch them.

256
00:12:51,400 --> 00:12:53,200
- Yes, Sir.
- Okay? Go ahead.

257
00:12:53,733 --> 00:12:55,067
Joaquin...

258
00:12:55,200 --> 00:12:57,733
I don't think you should
continue with the event.

259
00:12:57,867 --> 00:13:00,100
We should take
the bomb threat seriously!

260
00:13:00,233 --> 00:13:02,867
Sophia, stop believing that.

261
00:13:03,000 --> 00:13:05,667
If you're scared,
don't leave this room.

262
00:13:05,800 --> 00:13:07,400
Just stay here, okay?

263
00:13:08,200 --> 00:13:09,367
Oh.

264
00:13:09,500 --> 00:13:10,733
It's embarrassing
to my Vice-Mayor.

265
00:13:10,867 --> 00:13:12,900
I'll introduce her now.

266
00:13:13,033 --> 00:13:14,000
Wait, Dad...

267
00:13:14,133 --> 00:13:15,500
Vice Mayor?

268
00:13:16,233 --> 00:13:21,533
Leslie Del Mundo has agreed
to run as my vice mayor.

269
00:13:22,300 --> 00:13:23,400
Okay.

270
00:13:23,533 --> 00:13:25,167
Daddy...

271
00:13:28,433 --> 00:13:30,533
- Boss, Boss!
- Okay, we told him already.

272
00:13:30,667 --> 00:13:31,833
- It's okay, okay.
- Have you talked to him?

273
00:13:31,967 --> 00:13:33,000
Yeah Oh, wait, Boss.

274
00:13:33,133 --> 00:13:34,533
How did you know
there was a bomb there?

275
00:13:34,667 --> 00:13:35,667
Yes.

276
00:13:35,800 --> 00:13:37,367
I'll explain it to you later.

277
00:13:37,500 --> 00:13:38,400
- What?
- Okay, okay.

278
00:13:38,533 --> 00:13:40,000
Are we all complete?

279
00:13:40,133 --> 00:13:41,767
- Yes!
- Okay!

280
00:13:41,900 --> 00:13:44,400
You guys must have had
breakfast, right?

281
00:13:44,533 --> 00:13:46,500
- Hey!
- Oh?

282
00:13:46,633 --> 00:13:47,900
The has program has started?

283
00:13:48,033 --> 00:13:49,333
We also don't know what happen.

284
00:13:49,467 --> 00:13:51,733
- Are you sure you told them?
- We'll take care of it, Sir.

285
00:13:51,867 --> 00:13:52,767
That's it, that's it!
It's them.

286
00:13:52,900 --> 00:13:54,167
- It's the two of them!
- Why?

287
00:13:54,300 --> 00:13:57,867
We're arresting you
for violating...

288
00:13:58,033 --> 00:14:01,300
Presidential Decree 1727.

289
00:14:01,433 --> 00:14:03,167
- What's that?
- No bomb jokes allowed!

290
00:14:03,300 --> 00:14:04,733
- Oh, no, Sir!
- We're not joking, Sir!

291
00:14:04,867 --> 00:14:06,033
Boss, ask Boss Tonyo.

292
00:14:06,167 --> 00:14:07,333
Right, Boss?

293
00:14:07,467 --> 00:14:08,300
Sir, wait a minute.

294
00:14:08,433 --> 00:14:10,133
What if what
they're saying is true?

295
00:14:10,267 --> 00:14:11,500
Shouldn't the program
be stopped,

296
00:14:11,633 --> 00:14:12,667
for everyone's safety?

297
00:14:12,800 --> 00:14:14,167
<i> Yes!</i>

298
00:14:15,233 --> 00:14:16,267
- Noble!
- Ma'am?

299
00:14:16,400 --> 00:14:18,700
We need to talk
to Mayor's people.

300
00:14:18,833 --> 00:14:20,133
Come on.

301
00:14:20,933 --> 00:14:23,633
Shout out, Calabari!

302
00:14:26,267 --> 00:14:27,800
Are you ready?

303
00:14:29,600 --> 00:14:31,733
<i>Oh my, it's like
they haven't had breakfast yet.</i>

304
00:14:31,867 --> 00:14:34,033
One more time! Are you ready?

305
00:14:35,433 --> 00:14:36,633
<i> There, there!</i>

306
00:14:36,767 --> 00:14:38,567
<i> Let's shout together</i>

307
00:14:38,700 --> 00:14:41,200
<i>because he's going
to come out soon...</i>

308
00:14:41,333 --> 00:14:42,667
<i> El Hepe!</i>

309
00:14:42,800 --> 00:14:46,733
<i> El Hepe! El Hepe!</i>

310
00:14:53,100 --> 00:14:56,600
<i> El Hepe! El Hepe!</i>

311
00:14:56,733 --> 00:14:58,100
- El Hepe!
- Noble!

312
00:14:58,233 --> 00:15:00,033
Call the bomb squad.

313
00:15:00,167 --> 00:15:02,233
<i> Who will you vote for mayor?</i>

314
00:15:02,400 --> 00:15:08,033
- El Hepe! El Hepe!
- El Hepe! El Hepe!

315
00:15:08,167 --> 00:15:12,533
Here he is, our beloved mayor!

316
00:15:12,667 --> 00:15:14,300
Unwavering!

317
00:15:16,933 --> 00:15:20,033
Fighting for everyone!

318
00:15:21,733 --> 00:15:26,700
Mayor Joaquin "El Hepe"
Guerrero!

319
00:15:26,833 --> 00:15:28,833
A round of applause!

320
00:15:28,967 --> 00:15:33,633
El Hepe! El Hepe! El Hepe!

321
00:15:33,767 --> 00:15:34,767
Don't arrest them.

322
00:15:34,900 --> 00:15:36,933
These are just concerned
citizens.

323
00:15:37,100 --> 00:15:40,133
Why? Who are you, and why are
you interfering in this?

324
00:15:41,200 --> 00:15:42,433
- Arrest them!
- Let's go!

325
00:15:43,567 --> 00:15:45,667
- Arrest them!
- Run! Hurry up!

326
00:15:48,167 --> 00:15:51,733
Thank you all very much.

327
00:15:51,867 --> 00:15:53,433
Good morning.

328
00:15:54,567 --> 00:15:56,867
My heart feels good.

329
00:15:57,000 --> 00:15:59,367
I can feel,

330
00:15:59,800 --> 00:16:03,367
and see you supporting me.

331
00:16:06,167 --> 00:16:08,233
And I know,

332
00:16:08,400 --> 00:16:10,833
how much you contribute,

333
00:16:10,967 --> 00:16:13,367
to the development of Calabari.

334
00:16:15,333 --> 00:16:17,767
And because of this, I know...

335
00:16:18,800 --> 00:16:22,800
that you have great trust
in me as your mayor.

336
00:16:22,933 --> 00:16:24,500
And now,

337
00:16:25,133 --> 00:16:27,533
I will introduce to you,

338
00:16:27,667 --> 00:16:31,133
our new ally who will be
a partner,

339
00:16:31,267 --> 00:16:34,100
in the continuous progress
of Calabari...

340
00:16:35,567 --> 00:16:37,500
Our Vice Mayor,

341
00:16:37,633 --> 00:16:42,000
Vice Mayor Leslie Del Mundo!

342
00:16:42,167 --> 00:16:45,600
Del Mundo! Del Mundo!

343
00:16:45,733 --> 00:16:49,200
Del Mundo! Del Mundo!

344
00:16:49,333 --> 00:16:52,400
Amo, what's with Del Mundo?

345
00:16:52,533 --> 00:16:54,500
She should have said

346
00:16:54,633 --> 00:16:56,067
she was going
to the other side, right?

347
00:16:56,200 --> 00:16:58,867
Is it hard to say, Amo?

348
00:16:59,000 --> 00:17:01,400
That's how politics is.

349
00:17:01,533 --> 00:17:03,767
There are no real allies.

350
00:17:03,900 --> 00:17:06,033
I'd like to blow things up,
right?

351
00:17:11,333 --> 00:17:13,533
Hello? What's the update?

352
00:17:14,900 --> 00:17:17,133
Okay, Boss,
it's in place already.

353
00:17:17,267 --> 00:17:19,167
It's inside the flower,
in the middle of the stage.

354
00:17:37,300 --> 00:17:39,467
Thank you very much, Mayor.

355
00:17:39,600 --> 00:17:44,333
Calabari, are you ready
for continuous change?

356
00:17:45,067 --> 00:17:49,133
Are you ready
for back-to-back progress?

357
00:17:51,600 --> 00:17:55,400
Miss, did you see a man
wearing pink and a hat?

358
00:17:55,533 --> 00:17:56,833
Oh, no.

359
00:17:56,967 --> 00:17:58,133
I'm sorry.

360
00:17:58,267 --> 00:17:59,867
- Okay, thank you.
- Okay.

361
00:18:04,000 --> 00:18:05,400
Ma'am!

362
00:18:05,967 --> 00:18:07,367
I already called the bomb squad.

363
00:18:07,500 --> 00:18:09,033
Who are you looking for?

364
00:18:09,167 --> 00:18:11,733
Roman's guy, he's here.

365
00:18:11,867 --> 00:18:14,333
He probably planted
the bomb here.

366
00:18:14,467 --> 00:18:15,767
Ma'am, how did you say that?

367
00:18:15,900 --> 00:18:18,167
I saw him at Amo's house.

368
00:18:18,833 --> 00:18:20,633
I'm sure he's pretending
to be a worker here,

369
00:18:20,767 --> 00:18:21,633
so he can plant the bomb...

370
00:18:21,800 --> 00:18:23,700
without anyone noticing him.

371
00:18:23,833 --> 00:18:25,433
- Pretending to be what?
- I saw him.

372
00:18:25,567 --> 00:18:28,800
His t-shirt says RS Flower
Supply.

373
00:18:32,000 --> 00:18:33,833
That means it's possible...

374
00:18:34,633 --> 00:18:37,333
that the bomb
may be in the flowers!

375
00:18:37,467 --> 00:18:38,933
Come on, Noble!

376
00:18:42,133 --> 00:18:43,567
Son...

377
00:18:45,167 --> 00:18:46,733
Mom, what's that?

378
00:18:47,333 --> 00:18:50,500
Is Leslie Del Mundo going
to be daddy's vice mayor?

379
00:18:50,633 --> 00:18:52,900
Why did I find it out just now?

380
00:18:53,033 --> 00:18:56,167
It was supposed
to be a surprise.

381
00:18:56,333 --> 00:18:57,833
Surprise?

382
00:18:58,400 --> 00:18:59,867
I'm part of this campaign too.

383
00:19:00,000 --> 00:19:01,867
I'm part of this family too.

384
00:19:03,333 --> 00:19:05,933
- Your dad requested...
- What?

385
00:19:06,067 --> 00:19:07,600
Not tell me?

386
00:19:08,467 --> 00:19:10,033
To keep me out of it?

387
00:19:10,167 --> 00:19:11,833
I'm not sulking, Mom,

388
00:19:11,967 --> 00:19:13,500
but I'm just surprised.

389
00:19:23,533 --> 00:19:24,500
Faye!

390
00:19:24,633 --> 00:19:25,967
Who are you?

391
00:19:26,100 --> 00:19:27,900
Sir, you need
to get out of here.

392
00:19:28,033 --> 00:19:29,500
There's a bomb going off.

393
00:19:29,667 --> 00:19:32,100
Oh my gosh, Mommy, it's true
that there's a bomb.

394
00:19:32,233 --> 00:19:33,100
We have to go.

395
00:19:33,233 --> 00:19:35,400
- Let's go.
- Let's go, let's go.

396
00:19:35,533 --> 00:19:36,967
You know, to be honest,

397
00:19:37,100 --> 00:19:39,267
I've been serving
for a long time,

398
00:19:39,700 --> 00:19:42,167
but it's only now
that I feel, alive,

399
00:19:42,300 --> 00:19:44,533
it's only now that I am excited,

400
00:19:44,667 --> 00:19:48,133
because I'm on the right side.

401
00:19:48,267 --> 00:19:51,433
Noble, call Sir Tonyo!

402
00:19:57,300 --> 00:19:58,733
Hello, Noble?

403
00:19:58,867 --> 00:20:00,233
Where are you and Enriquez?

404
00:20:00,367 --> 00:20:03,267
We've found out
where the bomb is.

405
00:20:03,433 --> 00:20:05,767
It's in the plants on the stage.

406
00:20:08,600 --> 00:20:09,733
Give me that!

407
00:20:09,867 --> 00:20:13,967
I want you to know that
it's very important...

408
00:20:14,100 --> 00:20:15,000
- Boss!
- Ma'am?

409
00:20:15,133 --> 00:20:17,600
It's the Mayor,
I just need to talk to him.

410
00:20:17,733 --> 00:20:19,500
Ma'am, I'm sorry, you can't.

411
00:20:19,633 --> 00:20:21,700
Sir, I'm begging you,
there's a bomb.

412
00:20:21,833 --> 00:20:23,033
The people and the Mayor
are in danger.

413
00:20:23,167 --> 00:20:24,433
You need to evacuate them now!

414
00:20:24,567 --> 00:20:26,000
Ma'am, I'm really sorry.

415
00:20:26,133 --> 00:20:27,400
<i> You really can't.</i>

416
00:20:30,133 --> 00:20:32,000
Everyone, listen up.

417
00:20:32,133 --> 00:20:35,967
Evacuate this area because
a bomb is going to explode!

418
00:20:40,800 --> 00:20:42,500
Save yourselves!

419
00:20:42,633 --> 00:20:44,100
Get out of here!

420
00:20:44,233 --> 00:20:45,367
Here!

421
00:20:57,800 --> 00:20:59,933
Mayor, you are wounded!

422
00:21:00,067 --> 00:21:01,067
Come on!

423
00:21:01,200 --> 00:21:03,267
Let's get out of here! Hurry!

424
00:21:04,633 --> 00:21:07,067
Amo, Amo.

425
00:21:07,200 --> 00:21:08,800
Verns...

426
00:21:08,967 --> 00:21:11,500
I don't want to entertain
an interview reaction

427
00:21:11,633 --> 00:21:14,333
to Joaquin and Leslie's
announcement.

428
00:21:14,467 --> 00:21:16,333
I don't want to face
the press right now.

429
00:21:16,467 --> 00:21:19,867
Amo, there was an explosion,
at a political rally earlier.

430
00:21:20,000 --> 00:21:21,700
Oh, I was just watching
the livestream,

431
00:21:21,833 --> 00:21:22,933
And I can clearly see
him on the camera

432
00:21:23,067 --> 00:21:24,800
Sir Tonyo, I saw him clearly,
Amo.

433
00:21:24,933 --> 00:21:25,933
- He was there.
- Are you sure?

434
00:21:26,067 --> 00:21:27,567
Yes, Amo!

435
00:21:29,267 --> 00:21:32,533
Fortunately, no one
was seriously injured.

436
00:21:34,867 --> 00:21:36,333
Yes, by the way, Enriquez.

437
00:21:36,933 --> 00:21:38,667
How did you know...

438
00:21:38,800 --> 00:21:40,533
that the bomb
was in the flowers?

439
00:21:40,667 --> 00:21:43,467
Sir, Ma'am Enriquez saw someone
she recognized

440
00:21:43,633 --> 00:21:45,267
as Roman's person.

441
00:21:45,400 --> 00:21:48,000
And there he is, pretending
to be a flower supplier.

442
00:21:48,133 --> 00:21:49,900
Good job, Enriquez.

443
00:21:50,933 --> 00:21:53,133
How is Mayor Guerrero doing?

444
00:21:58,200 --> 00:21:59,933
Oh, I have missed calls
from the Chief..

445
00:22:00,067 --> 00:22:01,533
- Let me call him.
- Okay.

446
00:22:01,667 --> 00:22:04,033
You go ahead,
I'll follow you later.

447
00:22:06,233 --> 00:22:08,400
Sergeant Enriquez!

448
00:22:15,300 --> 00:22:17,000
Thank you very much.

449
00:22:18,067 --> 00:22:20,167
You guys are the ones
who brought my Daddy here.

450
00:22:20,300 --> 00:22:22,967
You saved
the two of us already.

451
00:22:31,233 --> 00:22:33,533
Joaquin,
how are you feeling?

452
00:22:35,667 --> 00:22:37,367
I'm okay, Sophia.

453
00:22:37,900 --> 00:22:41,267
I'm just grateful
that I'm still alive.

454
00:22:42,433 --> 00:22:44,600
I'm sorry,

455
00:22:44,733 --> 00:22:50,033
I should have listened to you
that there was a bomb.

456
00:22:50,200 --> 00:22:52,333
Joaquin, don't think about
that anymore.

457
00:22:52,467 --> 00:22:56,700
It was Glen
who warned us about it.

458
00:22:59,900 --> 00:23:02,267
Mayor, excuse me.

459
00:23:02,400 --> 00:23:04,433
Oh, the press downstairs...

460
00:23:04,567 --> 00:23:05,867
is still waiting
for your update.

461
00:23:06,000 --> 00:23:08,067
I also prepared a speech.

462
00:23:08,200 --> 00:23:10,067
Dad is still resting.

463
00:23:10,200 --> 00:23:12,067
I'll face them first.

464
00:23:12,200 --> 00:23:13,400
Let's go.

465
00:23:13,533 --> 00:23:14,967
Glen!

466
00:23:15,100 --> 00:23:16,600
Not you.

467
00:23:17,800 --> 00:23:19,533
Leslie...

468
00:23:19,667 --> 00:23:23,233
can you face the press, please?

469
00:23:27,233 --> 00:23:28,833
Of course, Mayor.

470
00:23:29,467 --> 00:23:31,300
We'll go ahead.

471
00:23:36,933 --> 00:23:38,300
<i> Get out of here!</i>

472
00:23:40,133 --> 00:23:42,500
Victor Santiago did that.

473
00:23:42,633 --> 00:23:46,800
Captain, we don't know that.

474
00:23:46,933 --> 00:23:50,433
What if it was done
by a terrorist?

475
00:23:50,567 --> 00:23:55,367
Oh my, he really did that
because he knows

476
00:23:55,533 --> 00:23:58,500
no one wants
to vote for him anymore.

477
00:23:59,433 --> 00:24:01,200
I agree with Captain.

478
00:24:01,333 --> 00:24:04,133
I thought Amo was okay,
but I was wrong.

479
00:24:04,267 --> 00:24:05,300
He's really not okay,

480
00:24:05,433 --> 00:24:07,467
and I won't vote for him.

481
00:24:07,600 --> 00:24:09,867
Good afternoon,
friends from the media.

482
00:24:10,533 --> 00:24:12,933
Following this tragic event,

483
00:24:13,067 --> 00:24:14,467
we want to assure you,

484
00:24:14,600 --> 00:24:16,867
that Mayor Joaquin Guerrero...

485
00:24:17,533 --> 00:24:19,100
is safe.

486
00:24:19,900 --> 00:24:26,000
This despicable act has
no place in the community.

487
00:24:26,133 --> 00:24:28,933
And we stand united
in condemning

488
00:24:29,100 --> 00:24:31,933
this senseless act
of distraction.

489
00:24:32,067 --> 00:24:33,067
We want to assure you,

490
00:24:33,200 --> 00:24:36,600
that we will work tirelessly
with the authorities.

491
00:24:36,733 --> 00:24:41,333
So that justice is served
and peace prevails.

492
00:24:41,467 --> 00:24:43,533
What are you doing here?

493
00:24:43,667 --> 00:24:44,300
- What are you...
- Glen...

494
00:24:44,433 --> 00:24:45,600
Boss!

495
00:24:45,733 --> 00:24:47,533
- Wait a minute!
- Don't, don't, don't.

496
00:24:47,667 --> 00:24:50,800
Did you come here to make sure
my dad is dead?

497
00:24:50,933 --> 00:24:52,000
You know, Godfather,

498
00:24:52,133 --> 00:24:53,900
I know you and dad have been
enemies for a long time,

499
00:24:54,033 --> 00:24:55,933
but I never thought
badly of you...

500
00:24:56,067 --> 00:24:57,100
until now!

501
00:24:57,233 --> 00:24:59,567
Glen, I have nothing to do
with what you're saying!

502
00:24:59,700 --> 00:25:01,633
Then who? Do you know who?

503
00:25:01,800 --> 00:25:04,167
If you're really desperate
to win this election,

504
00:25:04,300 --> 00:25:05,533
just target me!

505
00:25:05,667 --> 00:25:07,433
- You're such a bad person!
- Stop it!

506
00:25:07,567 --> 00:25:09,300
Glen, stop it!

507
00:25:09,433 --> 00:25:10,400
Amo...

508
00:25:10,533 --> 00:25:11,667
I'm sorry, Amo.

509
00:25:11,800 --> 00:25:13,367
You should leave now.

510
00:25:14,333 --> 00:25:15,233
Amo, let's go.

511
00:25:15,367 --> 00:25:17,067
Let's go, that's enough.

512
00:25:17,200 --> 00:25:19,033
VM, I'm sorry.

513
00:25:23,067 --> 00:25:28,100
Job well done to you two,
Conde, Enriquez.

514
00:25:28,233 --> 00:25:31,700
It's good that you anticipated
what was going to happen,

515
00:25:31,833 --> 00:25:33,767
and saved the Mayor.

516
00:25:33,900 --> 00:25:35,033
Wait a minute.

517
00:25:35,200 --> 00:25:38,667
How did you find out
about the bomb?

518
00:25:42,067 --> 00:25:44,400
I was on patrol earlier.

519
00:25:44,533 --> 00:25:48,300
Then I found out from
Mayor's supporters.

520
00:25:49,867 --> 00:25:54,767
Tonyo, don't you work
for your father, Amo?

521
00:25:55,633 --> 00:25:57,933
What are you doing
at the Mayor's rally?

522
00:25:58,567 --> 00:26:03,467
Robles, Tonyo is not obligated
to answer your question.

523
00:26:03,600 --> 00:26:07,633
Unless you are officially
investigating him

524
00:26:07,767 --> 00:26:10,067
about the explosion
that happened.

525
00:26:10,733 --> 00:26:12,867
Are you investigating him?

526
00:26:13,533 --> 00:26:15,833
No, Sir. I'm sorry.

527
00:26:19,367 --> 00:26:20,800
You can go, Tonyo.

528
00:26:22,300 --> 00:26:23,667
Okay, Bok.

529
00:26:25,767 --> 00:26:27,833
Amo, are you okay?

530
00:26:28,300 --> 00:26:29,833
- I'm okay.
- We can take you to the ER.

531
00:26:29,967 --> 00:26:31,233
- Okay, no need.
- We'll come with you.

532
00:26:31,367 --> 00:26:33,133
Oh, Tonyo.

533
00:26:33,267 --> 00:26:35,033
Why are you here?

534
00:26:35,467 --> 00:26:38,167
Oh, Verns, go ahead.

535
00:26:39,100 --> 00:26:40,533
- Are you sure, Amo?
- Yes, I'll follow.

536
00:26:40,667 --> 00:26:42,100
Okay.

537
00:26:46,600 --> 00:26:49,267
Verns told me
that you were there,

538
00:26:49,400 --> 00:26:52,133
when something exploded
at Joaquin's rally.

539
00:26:52,267 --> 00:26:53,400
I just wanted to know

540
00:26:53,533 --> 00:26:56,033
if you were okay
or if you were hurt.

541
00:26:56,167 --> 00:26:58,600
I've been calling you,
but you can't be reached.

542
00:26:58,733 --> 00:27:00,167
You shouldn't have come.

543
00:27:00,300 --> 00:27:02,800
The Mayor has a lot
of supporters here.

544
00:27:02,933 --> 00:27:04,633
We're leaving anyway.
Let's go, come on.

545
00:27:04,767 --> 00:27:06,433
Father, wait a minute.

546
00:27:06,567 --> 00:27:07,733
Wait...

547
00:27:07,867 --> 00:27:10,200
Did you have anything to do
with what happened?

548
00:27:13,833 --> 00:27:14,867
Lieutenant Paloma,

549
00:27:15,000 --> 00:27:16,967
what can Station 12 do for you?

550
00:27:17,133 --> 00:27:18,167
We need your help, Sir.

551
00:27:18,300 --> 00:27:20,833
Maybe the case I brought to you
will be solved sooner,

552
00:27:20,967 --> 00:27:22,233
than the one you have in hand!

553
00:27:22,367 --> 00:27:24,767
At least, we here at Station 12

554
00:27:24,900 --> 00:27:26,967
we don't need to ask for help
from other stations.

555
00:27:27,100 --> 00:27:28,867
They only prey on women.

556
00:27:29,000 --> 00:27:29,967
You two can't do it.

557
00:27:30,100 --> 00:27:31,333
Who will pretend to be
the victim?

558
00:27:31,467 --> 00:27:32,233
Lieutenant Conde.

559
00:27:32,367 --> 00:27:33,600
We're looking sexy today.

560
00:27:33,733 --> 00:27:34,467
Not really, Sir.

561
00:27:34,600 --> 00:27:35,600
After the case,

562
00:27:35,733 --> 00:27:37,567
maybe we can both go out.

563
00:27:37,700 --> 00:27:38,867
Welcome to Dubai.

564
00:27:39,000 --> 00:27:42,400
Conde, Enriquez, just to be
clear, Selena is our priority.

565
00:27:42,533 --> 00:27:44,033
Captain Pong Marasigan.

566
00:27:44,167 --> 00:27:45,500
Bok, I need your help.
